deletions.Query:
MERGE INTO deletions AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, $1[1] AS _meta, $1[2] AS "_meta/op", $1[3] AS flow_published_at
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= 1 AND l.id <= 3
WHEN MATCHED AND r."_meta/op"='d' THEN
	DELETE
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l._meta = r._meta, l."_meta/op" = r."_meta/op", l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at
WHEN NOT MATCHED and r."_meta/op"!='d' THEN
	INSERT (id, _meta, "_meta/op", flow_published_at)
	VALUES (r.id, r._meta, r."_meta/op", r.flow_published_at);

duplicate_keys_standard.Query:
MERGE INTO duplicate_keys_standard AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, NULLIF($1[1], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS _meta, $1[2] AS flow_published_at, $1[3] AS int, $1[4] AS str
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= 1 AND l.id <= 5
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l._meta = r._meta, l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at, l.int = r.int, l.str = r.str
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
	INSERT (id, _meta, flow_published_at, int, str)
	VALUES (r.id, r._meta, r.flow_published_at, r.int, r.str);

multiple_types.Query:
MERGE INTO multiple_types AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, NULLIF($1[1], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS _meta, NULLIF($1[2], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS array_int, $1[3] AS binary_field, $1[4] AS bool_field, $1[5] AS float_field, $1[6] AS flow_published_at, NULLIF($1[7], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS multiple, NULLIF($1[8], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS nested, $1[9] AS nullable_int, $1[10] AS str_field
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= 1 AND l.id <= 10
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l._meta = r._meta, l.array_int = r.array_int, l.binary_field = r.binary_field, l.bool_field = r.bool_field, l.float_field = r.float_field, l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at, l.multiple = r.multiple, l.nested = r.nested, l.nullable_int = r.nullable_int, l.str_field = r.str_field
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
	INSERT (id, _meta, array_int, binary_field, bool_field, float_field, flow_published_at, multiple, nested, nullable_int, str_field)
	VALUES (r.id, r._meta, r.array_int, r.binary_field, r.bool_field, r.float_field, r.flow_published_at, r.multiple, r.nested, r.nullable_int, r.str_field);

string_escaped_key.Query:
MERGE INTO string_escaped_key AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, NULLIF($1[1], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS _meta, $1[2] AS counter, $1[3] AS flow_published_at
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= '\\he \\ '' " `llo`' AND l.id <= '\\he \\ '' " `llo`'
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l._meta = r._meta, l.counter = r.counter, l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
	INSERT (id, _meta, counter, flow_published_at)
	VALUES (r.id, r._meta, r.counter, r.flow_published_at);
